Creating a table and column using Sql Quires  :

CREATE TABLE Player_Details(Player_Name VARCHAR(70),
								Player_NickName VARCHAR(50),
								Country VARCHAR(40),
								Player_DOB DATETIME,
								Player_Role VARCHAR(50),
								Player_ShirtNumber INT,
								Matches INT,
								Runs INT,
								Avarage FLOAT,
								Player_TopScore INT,
								Player_InstaId VARCHAR(50)
								)


ALTER : 

ALTER-ADD  : To adding new column.                                  syntax:  ALTER TABLE TABLENAME ADD COLUMNNAME DATATYPE

ALTER-ALTER : using this we can change the data type ..             syntax: ALTER TABLE TABLENAME ALTER COLUMN COLUMNNAME DATATYPE

ALTER-DROP : Using this can drop the column                         syntax: ALTER TABLE TABLENAME DROP COLUMN COLUMNNAME 




DROP  :
DROP is using for delete the Entire table ..                          syntax: DROP TABLE TABLENAME 



TRUNCATE:
TRUNCATE is using for to remove the data inside the table              Syntax: TRUNCATE TABE TABLENAME 

